{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CyNEHWmp7D6LtMq6GgAPCo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QNPGJMckn4G6uAbmnhiDBf","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/rollback.sh","content":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# rollback.sh — Revert ray namespace to the original baseline configuration.\n#\n# Baseline captured from cluster inspection:\n#   ray-worker  replicas : 1\n#   ray-head    image    : rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n#   ray-worker  image    : rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n#   ray-head    resources: none (limits/requests removed)\n#   ray-worker  resources: none (limits/requests removed)\n#   ray-head    Service  : ClusterIP, port 6379 (gcs) only — no dashboard port\n#\n# DO NOT run this script while the cluster is serving production traffic.\n# Review and confirm each step before executing.\n\nset -euo pipefail\n\nNAMESPACE=\"ray\"\nBASELINE_IMAGE=\"rayproject/ray:2.9.0\"\nWORKER_REPLICAS=1\n\necho \"=== Ray cluster rollback to baseline ===\"\n\n# 1. Scale ray-worker back to baseline replica count\necho \"[1/5] Scaling ray-worker to ${WORKER_REPLICAS} replica(s)...\"\nkubectl -n \"${NAMESPACE}\" scale deploy/ray-worker --replicas=\"${WORKER_REPLICAS}\"\n\n# 2. Revert ray-head image\necho \"[2/5] Reverting ray-head image to ${BASELINE_IMAGE}...\"\nkubectl -n \"${NAMESPACE}\" set image deploy/ray-head ray-head=\"${BASELINE_IMAGE}\"\n\n# 3. Revert ray-worker image\necho \"[3/5] Reverting ray-worker image to ${BASELINE_IMAGE}...\"\nkubectl -n \"${NAMESPACE}\" set image deploy/ray-worker ray-worker=\"${BASELINE_IMAGE}\"\n\n# 4. Remove any resource limits/requests added to either deployment\necho \"[4/5] Clearing resource limits and requests on ray-head and ray-worker...\"\nkubectl -n \"${NAMESPACE}\" patch deploy/ray-head --type=json \\\n  -p='[{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources\",\"value\":{}}]'\nkubectl -n \"${NAMESPACE}\" patch deploy/ray-worker --type=json \\\n  -p=